prenatal care or delivery, she will be less likely to disclose her drug or alcohol use to her 
health care provider if she believes she will be subject to criminal prosecution. Thus, her 
doctor or nurse will not have all of the information he or she needs to treat the woman and 
her subsequently born child. Again this will only serve to impede the long-term goal of 
ensuring the health and well-being of mothers and babies.") 
 
